                        data-module-name="utility-bar-module-print"></div></div></div></div></div><section id="module-position-OAr_hvJdt7c" class="storytopbar-bucket sponsored-series-topbar-module"><div class="full content-bar content-bar-top"><div class="head"><div class="title content-bar-block"><h3 class="content-bar-heading">This story is part of <a href="/topic/e1c511fc-81e8-4287-a43a-9a610572d25b/james-robertson/" class="content-bar-em content-bar-block-link">James Robertson</a></h3></div><div class="content-bar-block"><a href="/story/news/local/michigan/detroit/2015/02/19/james-robertson-detroit-walking-man-children-elementary-school-inspiration/23658897/"    class="content-bar-block-link" data-ht="topicbar1">Detroit&#39;s hard-walkin&#39; worker goes to school</a></div><div class="content-bar-block"><a href="/story/news/local/michigan/2015/02/19/walking-man-james-robertson-detroit/23641867/"    class="content-bar-block-link" data-ht="topicbar2">Kids write letters to Detroit&#39;s hard-walkin&#39; worker</a></div><div class="content-bar-block"><a href="/story/news/local/michigan/oakland/2015/01/31/detroit-commuting-troy-rochester-hills-smart-ddot-ubs-banker-woodward-buses-transit/22660785/"    class="content-bar-block-link" data-ht="topicbar3">Heart and sole: Detroiter walks 21 miles in work commute</a></div></div><span class="border"></span></div></section><section id="module-position-OAr_hvJSJVk" class="storytopbar-bucket story-headline-module"><h1 class="asset-headline" itemprop="headline">How we can start to fix our transit mess</h1></section><section id="module-position-OAr_hvI_x9M" class="storytopbar-bucket story-byline-module"><div class="asset-metabar" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><span itemprop="name" class="asset-metabar-author asset-metabar-item">
        By Megan Owens, Detroit Free Press guest writer
    </span><span class="asset-metabar-time asset-metabar-item nobyline">10:59 a.m. EST February 10, 2015</span></div></section><section id="module-position-OAr_hvJQiAA" class="storytopbar-bucket google-survey-module"></section><!-- p402_premium class is utilized by Google Consumer Surveys --><div class="asset-double-wide double-wide p402_premium" role="main" itemprop="articleBody"><div id="module-position-OAr_iKVX6YQ" class="story-asset story-metadata-asset"><div class="article-metadata-wrap"><section id="module-position-OAr_hvLLW4o" class="storymetadata-bucket expandable-photo-module"><aside itemprop="associatedMedia" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject" class="single-photo expandable-collapsed"><div class="image-wrap"><img class="expand-img-horiz" itemprop="url" src="http://www.gannett-cdn.com/-mm-/b7c3a02e5aa7be0873b69b6b6910e53dbc2f8677/c=194-0-3309-2336&amp;r=x404&amp;c=534x401/local/-/media/DetroitFreePress/2015/02/06/B9316145271Z.1_20150206213904_000_G1T9SLH67.1-0.jpg" alt="DFP oped Owens opt o (3).JPG" data-mycapture-src="http://www.gannett-cdn.com/media/DetroitFreePress/2015/02/06/B9316145271Z.1_20150206213904_000_G1T9SLH67.1-0.jpg" /><span class="toggle"></span><meta itemprop="name" content="DFP oped Owens opt o (3).JPG" /><span class="mycapture-small-btn mycapture-btn-with-text mycapture-expandable-photo-btn-small js-mycapture-btn-small">Buy Photo</span></div><p class="image-credit-wrap"><span class="js-caption-wrapper"><span class="cutline js-caption">Residents of metro Detroit communities that have opted out of SMART service must demand that their elected officials opt back in, for the good of the region.</span><meta itemprop="copyrightHolder" content="" /><span class="credit">(Photo: 2011 photo by MANDI WRIGHT/Detroit Free Press)</span></span><span class="mycapture-btn mycapture-btn-with-text mycapture-expandable-photo-btn-large js-mycapture-btn">Buy Photo</span></p></aside></section></div></div><div id="module-position-OAr_iKViGnk" class="story-asset inline-share-tools-asset"><div class="inline-share-tools asset-inline-share-tools asset-inline-share-tools-top"><span
        class="inline-share-btn inline-share-btn-facebook"
        data-share-method="facebook"
        data-uotrack="InlineShareFacebookBtn"><span class="inline-share-count inline-share-count-facebook">
            222
        </span><span class="inline-share-btn-label inline-share-btn-label-facebook">CONNECT</span></span><a
        class="inline-share-btn inline-share-btn-twitter"
        data-share-method="twitter"
        data-uotrack="InlineShareTwitterLink"
        data-popup-width="550"
        data-popup-height="450"
